 ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Goring","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the places in Oxfordshire and West Sussex named Goring, from Old English <i>Gāringas</i> ‘people of Gāra’, a short form of various compound names with the first element <i>gār</i> ‘spear’.","German (<b>Göring</b>): see   Goering  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Goering","meanings":["German (<b>Göring</b>):","variant of   Gehring  .","topographic name derived from Slavic <i>gora</i> ‘mountain, hill’. Compare   Goring  ."]},{"name":"Gorringe","meanings":["English (Surrey and Suffolk): variant of   Goring  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":8,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":17,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Goring was born in 1320, in Lancing, Sussex, England as the son of John de Goring IV. He married Miss Robert Goring about 1345, in England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1362, at the age of 42."},"et":{"1320–1362":"1320–1362","1317–1362":"1317–1362","1342–Male":"1342–Surnud","1344–Male":"1344–Surnud","1346–1411":"1346–1411","1285–1323":"1285–1323","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1323":"1323","1411":"1411","1344":"1344","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1342":"1342","about 1345":"umbes 1345","about 1344":"umbes 1344","about 1342":"umbes 1342","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Lancing, Sussex, England":"Lancing, Sussex, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1320–1362":"1320–1362","1317–1362":"1317–1362","1342–Male":"1342–Kuollut","1344–Male":"1344–Kuollut","1346–1411":"1346–1411","1285–1323":"1285–1323","1362":"1362","1285":"1285","1337":"1337","1346":"1346","1323":"1323","1411":"1411","1344":"1344","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1342":"1342","about 1345":"noin 1345","about 1344":"noin 1344","about 1342":"noin 1342","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Lancing, Sussex, England":"Lancing, Sussex, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1320–1362":"1320–1362","1317–1362":"1317–1362","1342–Male":"1342–Décédé","